---
const pageTitle = "Nirvana Being — Air Quality Monitoring | AG Systems";
const pageDescription =
  "Case study: a ground-up air quality monitoring system built by AG Systems for Nirvana Being — device concept, backend, and live environmental dashboard.";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="description" content={pageDescription} />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>

    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #f3eee5;
        --ink: #15130f;
        --body: #3b372f;
        --muted: #70675b;
        --quiet: #9b9080;
        --rule: rgba(21, 19, 15, 0.15);
        --rule-strong: rgba(21, 19, 15, 0.34);
        --black: #15130f;
        --white: #fffaf0;
        --max: 900px;
      }

      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--paper), #f6f1e8 46%, var(--paper));
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Segoe UI", Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }

      a { color: inherit; text-decoration: none; }

      .wrap { width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 48px)); margin: 0 auto; }

      .topbar {
        position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 30;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
        background: rgba(243, 238, 229, 0.9);
        backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
      }
      .nav {
        min-height: 64px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
      }
      .brand-name { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 760; letter-spacing: -0.045em; }
      .backlink { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); border-bottom: 1px solid transparent; padding-bottom: 2px; }
      .backlink:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); }

      .label {
        margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--muted);
        font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.07em; text-transform: uppercase;
      }
      .label::before {
        content: ""; display: inline-block; width: 28px; height: 1px;
        margin-right: 10px; vertical-align: middle; background: var(--rule-strong);
      }

      h1, h2 { font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", ui-serif, serif; font-weight: 520; }

      .hero { padding: 56px 0 40px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
      h1 {
        margin: 0; font-size: clamp(38px, 5vw, 64px);
        line-height: 0.98; letter-spacing: -0.055em; max-width: 760px;
      }
      .hero-copy {
        max-width: 680px; margin: 20px 0 0; color: var(--body);
        font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.55; letter-spacing: -0.015em;
      }

      .facts {
        margin: 32px 0 0; padding: 0; list-style: none;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); max-width: 680px;
      }
      .facts li {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 130px 1fr; gap: 18px;
        padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); font-size: 14px;
      }
      .facts span { color: var(--muted); }
      .facts strong { font-weight: 650; }

      .section { padding: 44px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
      h2 { margin: 0 0 16px; font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px); letter-spacing: -0.05em; line-height: 1.02; }
      .section p { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 0 14px; color: var(--body); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; }

      .layer-list { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); margin-top: 24px; }
      .layer {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 0.4fr 1fr; gap: 32px;
        padding: 18px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      }
      .layer h3 { margin: 0; font-size: 18px; letter-spacing: -0.035em; font-weight: 690; }
      .layer p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.55; }

      .quote {
        margin: 24px 0 0; padding: 26px;
        background: var(--black); color: var(--white); max-width: 680px;
      }
      .quote p {
        margin: 0; font-family: Georgia, ui-serif, serif;
        font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.4; color: var(--white);
      }
      .quote footer { margin-top: 14px; font-size: 13px; color: rgba(255, 250, 240, 0.6); }

      .cta { padding: 48px 0 64px; }
      .cta p { max-width: 620px; margin: 0 0 22px; color: var(--body); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; }
      .button {
        min-height: 40px; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
        padding: 0 16px; border: 1px solid var(--black); background: var(--black); color: var(--white);
        font-size: 13px; font-weight: 650;
      }
      .button:hover { opacity: 0.86; }
      .button-ghost { background: transparent; color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--rule-strong); margin-left: 8px; }
      .button-ghost:hover { background: var(--black); color: var(--white); border-color: var(--black); opacity: 1; }

      .footer { padding: 22px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); color: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; }
      .footer-inner { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 18px; flex-wrap: wrap; }

      @media (max-width: 720px) {
        .wrap { width: min(100% - 28px, var(--max)); }
        .layer { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 8px; }
        .facts li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header class="topbar">
      <div class="wrap nav">
        <a class="brand-name" href="/">AG Systems</a>
        <a class="backlink" href="/#systems">← Back to Working Systems</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="wrap">
          <p class="label">Case study — Client deployment</p>
          <h1>Air quality monitoring for Nirvana Being.</h1>
          <p class="hero-copy">
            Nirvana Being needed live air-quality visibility tied to their brand — not an off-the-shelf monitor
            with someone else's app. AG Systems built the system end to end: the monitoring concept, the data
            flow, the backend, and the public-facing dashboard.
          </p>

          <ul class="facts" aria-label="Project facts">
            <li><span>Client</span><strong>Nirvana Being</strong></li>
            <li><span>Type</span><strong>Connected product + live dashboard</strong></li>
            <li><span>Scope</span><strong>Device concept, backend, web layer</strong></li>
            <li><span>Status</span><strong>Deployed — <a href="https://nirvanayours.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule-strong)">live dashboard</a></strong></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="wrap">
          <h2>The problem</h2>
          <p>
            Air quality is central to Nirvana Being's offering, but the data behind it lived in disconnected
            tools. There was no single live view that the business owned, matched their brand, and could be
            shown to customers.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="wrap">
          <h2>What was built</h2>
          <div class="layer-list">
            <div class="layer">
              <h3>Monitoring concept</h3>
              <p>The physical air-quality measurement approach — what to measure, where, and how readings flow out of the device layer.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="layer">
              <h3>Data flow and backend</h3>
              <p>Sensor readings collected, structured, and stored so the dashboard always reflects current conditions.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="layer">
              <h3>Live dashboard</h3>
              <p>A public environmental dashboard on the client's own domain, presenting the readings in their brand.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="layer">
              <h3>Web layer</h3>
              <p>The commercial-facing site structure around the dashboard, built for the client to operate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- TODO: fill in real numbers before publishing this section, or delete it.
           Examples of numbers worth using: readings logged per day, days of continuous
           uptime, number of monitored locations. Do not publish placeholder numbers. -->
      <!--
      <section class="section">
        <div class="wrap">
          <h2>In numbers</h2>
          <p>[X] readings per day · [X] days continuous operation · [X] locations monitored</p>
        </div>
      </section>
      -->

      <!-- TODO: ask Nirvana Being for a one-line quote and their preferred attribution,
           then uncomment. A real named quote is the strongest element on this page. -->
      <!--
      <section class="section">
        <div class="wrap">
          <h2>From the client</h2>
          <div class="quote">
            <p>"[Client quote here.]"</p>
            <footer>[Name, role] — Nirvana Being</footer>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      -->

      <section class="cta">
        <div class="wrap">
          <h2>Need a system like this?</h2>
          <p>
            The same method applies to any business that needs a connected product, a live dashboard,
            or an operational backend built around how it actually runs.
          </p>
          <a class="button" href="mailto:me@aryadhargupta.com">Start a Project</a>
          <a class="button button-ghost" href="/#systems">See other systems</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="wrap footer-inner">
        <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} AG Systems.</span>
        <span>A technology systems company by Aryadhar Gupta.</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
